04:49.600 --> 04:52.040
Give me till the end of the day,
this thing goes away.

04:52.200 --> 04:56.200
What're you talking about? We're
gonna have to make this thing go...

04:56.960 --> 05:00.320
- Heard you guys found a crispy critter.
- It's a miracle he's still alive.

05:00.480 --> 05:03.640
Must've had it coming. You gotta
piss somebody off to have them...

05:03.800 --> 05:07.120
...torture you and stick you in a trunk.
- Nobody deserves that.

05:07.280 --> 05:09.000
- He was probably a rat.
- Hey!

05:10.000 --> 05:11.240
- Back off!
- Cut it out!

05:11.440 --> 05:13.640
- Julien's not a rat.
- They run in packs now?

05:13.800 --> 05:15.400
- What is your problem?
- Vic!

05:16.080 --> 05:17.960
Hey!
Hey!

05:18.120 --> 05:20.000
Let's not make this
into a bigger mess.

05:22.040 --> 05:24.960
Come on.
Come on!

05:28.000 --> 05:33.360
Lay low, man. Do your work.
Leave this thing to me.

05:41.880 --> 05:43.040
Hey.

05:43.840 --> 05:47.040
Hey! I'm still here.

05:47.760 --> 05:49.400
- Julien...
- I hear you.

05:49.560 --> 05:52.960
- Well, you gotta help me out.
- Nothing I can do.

05:53.160 --> 05:56.120
- How did that cop know about us?
- I don't know.

06:03.560 --> 06:06.960
Pulled some strings.
Got you released until your court date.

06:07.160 --> 06:09.040
- You did?
- Yeah.

06:09.520 --> 06:11.520
I just need help with one thing first.

06:11.680 --> 06:14.160
I'm filling out my report,
and I'm a little confused.

06:14.960 --> 06:18.640
When I busted in, it looked like you had
some cop's dick in your mouth.

06:18.840 --> 06:21.400
That can't be right.
Can it?

06:21.920 --> 06:23.880
You got something to say,
say it to me.

06:24.080 --> 06:28.400
Okay. It's easy to make a mistake,
especially on a bust.

06:28.560 --> 06:32.720
You think you see someone pocketing
coke instead of boxes of ammo.

06:33.320 --> 06:36.480
- It can be confusing.
- He's not confused about anything.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.520
- I'm not taking back my statement.
- See?

06:40.560 --> 06:44.040
And what you're saying
that he and me did, it never happened.

06:44.640 --> 06:46.320
It never happened.

06:46.520 --> 06:49.240
What? Julien. Julien!

06:50.120 --> 06:53.640
- You heard him. It never happened.
- He needs me.

06:53.800 --> 06:57.200
- Aren't you full of yourself? It's over.
- That's not what he said.

06:57.360 --> 06:59.920
That's what I say. He's got a lot
on his mind right now.

07:00.080 --> 07:03.400
He doesn't need you
complicating things. Stay away.

07:03.560 --> 07:06.600
- You can't keep us apart.
- I've seen your sheet.

07:06.760 --> 07:10.040
Small-time con men like you
only care about themselves.

07:10.200 --> 07:11.640
Yeah, well, he cares about me.

07:11.840 --> 07:15.160
You don't want me hauling you in every
week. That's what you care about.

07:15.640 --> 07:17.720
So cut him off.

07:22.040 --> 07:24.400
Oh, man, look at this guy.

07:24.560 --> 07:27.960
I ever get that bad,
pull the plug with both hands.

07:28.120 --> 07:31.000
- Not me.
- What? You'd want that?

07:31.160 --> 07:33.280
No, but it beats the alternative.

07:33.440 --> 07:36.840
Just keep my machines juiced
until the Hoover Dam's out of business.

07:37.000 --> 07:40.200
- Detectives.
- Dr. Crawford. How's the poor sap?

07:40.360 --> 07:43.400
Third-degree burns over 60 percent
of his body. He's gonna die.

07:43.880 --> 07:45.680
Here are his things.

07:46.680 --> 07:49.560
The skin showed traces of red
phosphorus and hydrogen chloride.

07:49.720 --> 07:53.160
- He blew himself up in a meth lab.
- I'm seeing two, three of these a month.

07:53.320 --> 07:57.520
Every bozo from here to San
Bernardino thinks he can cook crank.

07:57.680 --> 08:00.040
Don't know
what you're doing, boom.

08:00.200 --> 08:02.400
Meth. Courtesy of Cupid.

08:04.520 --> 08:06.600
- How lovely.
- Meth's the drug of the day.

08:06.760 --> 08:08.800
We've got a few ODs in the ER
right now.

08:09.280 --> 08:11.680
Could you take us down there,
give us a look?

08:13.360 --> 08:16.080
- Oh, he's tweaking.
- Third one today.

08:16.240 --> 08:19.320
- Could I see the patient's belongings?
- Over here.

08:20.520 --> 08:23.040
May we see
the patient's belongings please?

08:23.400 --> 08:24.800
Thank you.

08:24.960 --> 08:26.920
- Call me if you get any more.
- I will.

08:27.080 --> 08:28.480
Cupid's busy.

08:28.640 --> 08:31.760
Looks like our mummy cooked up some
crap before blowing himself up.

08:31.920 --> 08:34.960
Let's hope he's dumb and lazy.
No telling how much he churned out.

08:35.120 --> 08:37.000
Got another college kid.

08:38.799 --> 08:42.120
- How do you want to play this?
- We both have our own ways that work.

08:42.280 --> 08:44.680
- Why don't we just take turns.
- Take turns?

08:44.840 --> 08:46.880
We follow one lead your way,
next one my way.

08:47.040 --> 08:49.320
Your way's not gonna land me
in the papers, is it?

08:49.480 --> 08:52.520
- Don't believe everything you read.
- Okay. Who goes first?

08:52.680 --> 08:55.560
- Ladies go first.
- All I know is the ID of the driver...

08:55.720 --> 08:58.400
...so let's start with his family.
- Lead the way.

08:58.600 --> 08:59.920
- David.
- Jorge.

09:00.080 --> 09:03.640
- There's no turning back, huh?
- I know I've burned some bridges.

09:03.800 --> 09:07.040
- Now's the time to build new ones.
- How so?

09:07.200 --> 09:08.560
The good news.

09:08.720 --> 09:11.840
This headline is exactly what we
needed to brand you for the voters.

09:12.000 --> 09:14.120
- It came out well.
- I've decided to back you...

09:14.280 --> 09:16.040
...for City Council.

09:16.680 --> 09:20.480
I was hoping that's what this
was about. Thank you.

09:20.640 --> 09:23.400
I would like you and Aurora to join me
for dinner tomorrow.

09:25.040 --> 09:26.880
You can meet
the rest of your team then.

09:27.040 --> 09:30.400
- I have a team?
- We have a lot of work ahead of us.

09:30.560 --> 09:34.840
The celebration on Cinco de Mayo will
make a good coming-out party for you.

09:35.000 --> 09:39.600
Jorge. I promise, I'm not in this to lose.

09:39.800 --> 09:41.160
You can't afford to.

09:44.520 --> 09:46.680
Don't believe everything
you read.

09:46.840 --> 09:49.240
You gotta wonder where they
come up with this stuff.

09:49.400 --> 09:52.440
- Anything break yet?
- No.

09:53.840 --> 09:56.680
There's a crack den on Temple
due for a toss. Want to hit it?

09:56.840 --> 10:00.680
I wish I could.
I've gotta go over some open files.

10:00.840 --> 10:02.760
Alrighty then.

10:04.320 --> 10:05.640
Danny!

10:06.640 --> 10:08.640
How was the sergeant's test?

10:08.800 --> 10:11.560
I don't know. It's gonna be close.
I kind of froze a little.

10:11.720 --> 10:13.080
I'll bet you did great.

10:13.240 --> 10:16.320
Listen, pass or fail, I do want
to thank you for tutoring me.

10:16.480 --> 10:18.600
- Can I buy you dinner tomorrow night?
- Sure.

10:18.800 --> 10:21.320
Great. Tomorrow night.
You pick the place.

10:24.360 --> 10:27.360
- Can I help you with that?
- Sure, yeah.

10:27.520 --> 10:30.960
- Can I help you?
- Yes. I'm looking for Det. Gannon.

10:31.120 --> 10:33.920
I've been leaving him messages
for the last two months.

10:34.080 --> 10:36.840
Det. Gannon retired last year.

10:38.160 --> 10:41.880
Well, he was investigating a case.
My husband was murdered.

10:44.640 --> 10:48.160
- Here, have a seat.
- Thank you.

10:50.480 --> 10:52.000
I haven't heard anything in ages.

10:52.160 --> 10:54.760
I couldn't understand
why he wasn't returning my calls.

10:54.920 --> 10:56.920
- What's your husband's name?
- Kyle Kelner.

10:57.080 --> 10:59.800
I'll pull the file.
I'll be right back.

11:02.560 --> 11:05.200
So you lost your husband.

11:06.280 --> 11:09.480
- Year ago today.
- I'm so sorry.

11:09.640 --> 11:13.200
I don't understand. I mean,
why would Andy run from the police?

11:13.360 --> 11:19.160
He had a burn victim in his trunk
and methamphetamine in his pocket.

11:20.080 --> 11:22.680
This doesn't make any sense.

11:23.080 --> 11:25.120
This is from my daughter's
rubber-stamp kit.

11:25.280 --> 11:27.560
You didn't know
your husband was involved in this?

11:27.720 --> 11:30.560
He's a web-page designer,
not a drug dealer.

11:30.720 --> 11:33.560
He and his friend Eric
have been looking for jobs...

11:33.720 --> 11:36.360
...ever since the company
they worked for had gone bust.

11:36.520 --> 11:40.320
- Who's Eric?
- They went to college together.

11:40.520 --> 11:43.200
I tried to reach him
when I saw the chase on TV...

11:43.400 --> 11:45.080
...but I can't get ahold of him.

11:45.240 --> 11:47.840
I'm afraid I might know
where to find Eric.

11:50.040 --> 11:54.640
- I can't even look at him like that.
- It was a meth-lab explosion.

11:54.800 --> 11:56.280
What?

11:56.880 --> 11:58.880
Meth lab?

11:59.360 --> 12:02.200
I knew that my brother
was having money problems.

12:02.360 --> 12:04.400
You know, but how was I supposed
to help him?

12:04.600 --> 12:09.720
He's the one who went to college.
Now they're asking me to end his life.

12:11.840 --> 12:13.640
What do I do?

12:15.320 --> 12:17.040
Thanks for standing up
for me earlier.

12:17.200 --> 12:19.760
That's what partners do.
Even if you don't agree with them.

12:19.920 --> 12:22.360
- Don't agree with them?
- Look, this is a brotherhood.

12:22.520 --> 12:23.880
Everybody knows that but you.

12:24.040 --> 12:26.960
- You don't know what I been through.
- Because you don't tell me.

12:27.120 --> 12:30.160
Decide if you wanna stay partners.
If you do, start opening up.

12:30.320 --> 12:33.440
If you don't, talk to Aceveda.
Car's clean.

12:36.680 --> 12:39.240
He turned me down when
I asked him for a new partner.

12:39.400 --> 12:42.120
Maybe he'll give you
a different answer.

12:42.280 --> 12:44.720
- Here's an unserved warrant.
- Year-old lottery ticket.

12:44.880 --> 12:47.800
Weight Watchers coupon.
Like that lard-ass would ever use it.

12:47.960 --> 12:50.080
He just dumped
his desk drawer into this box.

12:50.240 --> 12:54.680
Clock ran out on this case a year ago.
I'm not shovelling ice off the clue trail.

12:54.840 --> 12:57.480
- Well, we owe it to her.
- No, Gannon owes her.

12:57.640 --> 12:58.960
You want me to fly solo?

13:00.160 --> 13:03.480
No, man. Looks like this
is the only action I'm gonna get today.

13:03.680 --> 13:06.200
- Excuse me?
